[The illness could be scrub typhus, which is not tickborne. A tickborne spotted fever with a primary eschar as described here would not be caused by _Rickettsia rickettsii_, the cause of Rocky Mountain spotted fever, but rather another of the spotted fever rickettsia group that is associated with an eschar. ProMED would appreciate more information regarding the specific rickettsia involved. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2980237,9803.]
